fields.author: Customers are saying
fields.text: Customers express satisfaction with the Galaxy Tab A9+ 11" 128GB - Wi-Fi, particularly its affordability, large screen size, and extended battery life. Many users also appreciate the tablet's fast performance and responsive app usage. However, some customers have noted the absence of a power adapter in the packaging.

fields.author: Nice
fields.text: A giant leap from the a7 I had. Thank goodness for the 90ghz, much better. It serves most games but I wouldn't recommended for extreme frame rate games. It's fast as long as you don't have 10+ apps open at once. Battery life is just a smidge behind the a7 but it's more powerful so it still last me 3 or 4 days. Overall I hand it a A- for it's price range.

fields.author: The Verge
fields.text: The 2024 Surface Pro (dubbed the “11th Edition”) is sleek, thin, and boasts a beautiful OLED screen. Powered by Qualcomm’s Snapdragon X chips, it offers long battery life. However, Arm compatibility isn’t flawless yet, and the Flex Keyboard is pricey. Still, if you’re after a premium 2-in-1, this Surface feels fresh and modern. Windows Central calls it a stunning achievement with excellent performance and battery life, making it a must-recommend device.

fields.author: David
fields.text:
After a week of moderate use, I believe this is one of Apple’s best products to date! Compact, powerful, and practical, this newest M4 iPad Pro checks off a lot of boxes for users needing something that will get them through the entire day. Coupled with the pro keyboard case, it serves as a nice laptop replacement for normal, everyday use, breezing through all of your operations and media consumption. The display’s unmatched clarity and brightness alone is worth everything, making mobile games come to life.

Some of the best things that I love about this tablet are: the new M4 chipset (incredibly powerful and efficient); the tandem OLED display (very bright and vibrant colors); sleek, thin, and featherweight design, and all-day battery life. I haven’t connected mine to a mobile plan just yet, but have been testing out mobile hotspot via my cell phone, and I’m getting over 14 hours of constant video use! Insanity!

fields.author: Serhio
fields.text: I recently visited 'MyShop' in Saint Petersburg, to purchase an MSI laptop, and I couldn't be happier with the service I received. The staff was incredibly attentive and knowledgeable, helping me navigate through the various models and specifications to find the perfect fit for my needs. I ultimately chose the MSI katana a15 Stealth, and it has been an amazing investment. The laptop boasts a sleek and professional design, perfect for both gaming and work. It features a powerful amd ryzen 9 processor, 16GB of RAM, and an NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4070 graphics card, making it a beast for gaming and heavy-duty tasks. The 15.6-inch Full HD display is vibrant and crisp, and the 244Hz refresh rate ensures smooth and fluid visuals. i really enjoy editing in adobe. The purchasing process at Best Buy was seamless. The staff answered all my questions and even provided some useful tips for maintaining the laptop. They also offered a great warranty plan, which gave me peace of mind.

fields.author: MohammadM
fields.text:
I was really excited for this laptop with the Intel Core Ultra CPU for their efficiency cores. I travel a lot for work so battery life is super important, but also appreciate the ability to play some games back at the hotel. 

+ Screen is gorgeous 
+ Felt light for its size
+ I didn't hear any fan noise during the day

+/- I'm realistically going to get 8 hours of battery doing work and 6-7hrs before feeling worried about finding a power outlet. I don't need to do anything intense on my machine, just lots of Microsoft Office stuff, gmail and video meetings. Most of the online reviewers use benchmarking tools like Modern Office, or run netflix related streaming tests for battery life, but that did really cover my use case.
+/- I miss windows hello with camera, but the fingerprint reader is real fast
+/- Giant touchpad almost seems too big

- Teams and Zoom calls drained battery fast. I'm usually going to be connected to a powerline if I'm taking video calls.

fields.author: user
fields.text: Customers are delighted by the MacBook Pro 14" Laptop's long battery life, powerful performance, stunning display, and sleek design. They appreciate its portability, powerful M3 chip, and ample storage. Video editors praise its ability to handle 4K video editing with ease. The easy setup process is also a plus. On the downside, some customers find the price to be a bit steep, especially for those who want more memory.

This new one is by far the best - faster than a speeding bullet. I've been importing video files and I am amazed at how quickly they are transferred. I have not started crunching the compression of new videos yet, but I have no doubt that this machine will be faster than anything else. I had been wanting to move up to a new MBP for some time but I resented needing dongles for everything - finally we are back to a set of the most useful connecters  built in. I find the fingerprint ID very useful. Safari is solid and glitch-free so far.  More than anything, the battery

fields.text: he most frustrating PC experience I've ever had. I've been using a Mac to complete some work, and it was working nicely. After using Windows PCs and Chromebooks, I can not fathom why anyone would make operating a computer so incredibly frustrating to use. Want to change or do anything? Type in your password. fields.author: JasonC
fields.text:
recently upgraded to the Apple Studio Display, and I couldn't be happier with my decision! From the moment I unboxed it, the sleek design and premium build quality were evident. The 27-inch 5K Retina display is simply breathtaking. The colors are vibrant, and the sharpness is unparalleled—perfect for graphic design and video editing.

The True Tone technology adapts beautifully to different lighting conditions, providing a comfortable viewing experience throughout the day. The built-in speakers deliver impressive sound quality, and the FaceTime HD camera ensures I look my best on video calls.

Setting it up was a breeze, and the seamless integration with my Mac is a huge plus. Whether I'm working or enjoying some downtime, the Studio Display has transformed my workspace into a creative haven.

Overall, I highly recommend the Apple Studio Display to anyone looking for a top-tier monitor. It’s worth every penny for the clarity, functionality, and aesthetic appeal.

fields.text: To be completely honest I’ve owned the first gen for about 2 years now and it’s the exact same mouse nothing has changed. Maybe I’m just so used to how my first one feels but I didn’t even use it more than once before I returned it to find a better alternative. fields.author: AndreiC
fields.text: The mouse had a good shape and the build quality felt nice. The grip tape was very good surprisingly and the mouse feet were very smooth. The clicks felt crispy but actuation on them is a bit heavy and takes time getting used to. On a standard 240hz monitor, the upgrade to the 2k polling rate isn’t even much of an upgrade considering how unnoticeable it is so I would recommend staying at 1k for longer battery life. The usb-c coord is nice and much better than micro usb found on old ones however it still is a rubber cable. Overall, it’s a good mouse and I would recommend getting it if you don’t currently own the older model.
